    <section class="creature-page">
      <div class="creature-hero">
        <div class="creature-info">
          <h1>Aura</h1>
          <div class="creature-meta">
            <p><strong>Possible Name:</strong> AURAEON (Aura + aeon, eternity, pronounced “or-EE-on”) or simply AURA.</p>
            <p><strong>Inspiration:</strong> Butterfly and flying fish, plus a custom-designed logo.</p>
            <p><strong>Type:</strong> Ancient spiritual creature.</p>
            <p><strong>Origin:</strong> A peaceful, dreamy, pure, calm world.</p>
            <p><strong>Reference:</strong> Inspired in part by the world feeling from Avatar: The Way of Water.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="creature-illustration">
          <img class="aura-main-image" src="/creature%20pictures/Aura1.png" alt="Aura concept illustration">
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="creature-related">
        <h2>Midterm Presentation Notes</h2>
        <div class="aura-notes-layout">
          <div class="creature-meta aura-notes-text">
            <h3>Concept and World-Building</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Aura creatures are native to a pure and peaceful world.</li>
              <li>They are very ancient, highly intelligent, and wise.</li>
              <li>They are very rare and on the verge of extinction because they can only survive in pure environments.</li>
              <li>They are outside the normal food chain (or highest in it) because they feed on energy and aura, not flesh.</li>
              <li>They have no natural predators or prey, but humans desire them.</li>
              <li>Their bodies are mostly transparent, allowing aura to fill and flow through them.</li>
              <li>The purer and calmer the environment, the stronger the energy they can absorb.</li>
              <li>When near strong aura, they absorb and merge with it.</li>
              <li>They often live in herds.</li>
              <li>Reproduction cycle: they are unisex; when an old Aura dies, it transforms into an egg and regrows into a young Aura.</li>
              <li>Younger Aura follow older ones; older Aura are more powerful and hold stronger aura/energy.</li>
              <li>They are neutral spiritual beings and avoid interfering with worldly conflicts.</li>
              <li>They have relatives of the same species in different colors, each connected to specific aura traits (love, hope, calm, etc.).</li>
              <li>In emergencies, they seek out their relatives, but usually remain with their own group.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Character Turnarounds</h3>
            <p><strong>2D Turnarounds:</strong> Sketches created in class (2.13).</p>
            <p><strong>3D Turnarounds / Modeling Process:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Initial primitive and workflow: cube, scale, extrude, subdivide, loop cuts (Command + R), then adjust to match drafts.</li>
              <li>Built half of the body first, then mirrored.</li>
              <li>Used sculpt mode for texture/detail.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>1st Draft Challenges:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Mirror seam created an unwanted center line.</li>
              <li>The form felt rigid instead of floating.</li>
              <li>Antenna shapes were hard to build.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>2nd Draft (after office hours with Jiayi):</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Enabled X mirror workflow.</li>
              <li>Used a sphere for the body.</li>
              <li>Used curves for antennae.</li>
              <li>Increased subdivisions and loop cuts for better topology.</li>
              <li>Used sculpt mode for more detail.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Next Steps:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Add more inner structure (vein-like forms).</li>
              <li>Add transparent texture and color treatment.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Camera Stills & Feedback</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Prepare 3–5 still images from different camera angles.</li>
              <li>Animation idea: transform into an egg, then regrow while spreading/merging with water.</li>
              <li>Movement idea: show a herd of Aura swimming/floating together.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Assignment Sections Included</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Concept and world-building</li>
              <li>Character turnarounds</li>
              <li>Camera stills</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <aside class="aura-side-images">
            <img src="/creature%20pictures/Aura2.jpg" alt="Aura second concept image">
            <img src="/creature%20pictures/Aura3.png" alt="Aura third concept image">
            <img src="/creature%20pictures/AuraWorld.png" alt="Aura world design image">
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="about" class="about-bar">
